<h2>Gameplay Mechanics</h2>
<p>The core structure follows FNAF 2 — survive the night in your security office using cameras, a flashlight, and the Freddy mask. But nearly every mechanic has been reworked to create a more strategic and visually dynamic experience.</p>

<h3>The Animatronics</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Toy Bonnie & Toy Chica:</strong> They approach through the vents, just like the original. Put on the mask when they enter the office — but now you get animated entry sequences that give you a slightly larger window to react. Wait until they lock eyes with you before reaching for the mask.</li>
    <li><strong>Toy Freddy:</strong> Completely reworked. He laughs and heads for one of 4 fuse boxes marked with green circles on the cameras. Find him and hit him with the camera flashlight. If he reaches a box, the lights go out and the Puppet's music box gets locked. You'll need to solve a quick mini-puzzle on the cameras to restore power.</li>
    <li><strong>The Puppet:</strong> The music box mechanic returns, but with slower drain to account for Toy Freddy's interference. Keep it wound or face the consequences.</li>
    <li><strong>Withered Foxy:</strong> Appears in the hallway. Flash him repeatedly with your mouse — same principle as the original, but the animations make him far more intimidating.</li>
    <li><strong>Mangle:</strong> Enters through the main hallway, climbs to the ceiling causing camera static, then drops her head down twice — requiring the mask each time. She's one of the most stressful encounters because her static noise drowns out Toy Freddy's laugh, making multitasking a nightmare.</li>
    <li><strong>Withered Bonnie, Chica & Freddy:</strong> They come down the hallway with intimidating new animations. Mask up when they enter the office.</li>
    <li><strong>Balloon Boy:</strong> Can appear through either vent. Shine your light on him to scare him away. If he gets in, he steals your batteries and Foxy becomes an instant kill.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Later Night Threats</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Shadow Bonnie (Night 5+):</strong> Shadows appear on camera feeds blocking essential buttons — camera switches, flashlight, and the music box. Click them to clear them. They represent the Puppet actively trying to stop you from uncovering the truth.</li>
    <li><strong>Golden Freddy (Night 5):</strong> When he appears, look away to the cameras. Stare too long and the hallucinations begin.</li>
</ul>

</div>

